        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to support the establishment of dairy units with 10 Gir cows. Through this scheme, capital subsidy and back-ended subsidy are provided to beneficiaries via bank finance and NABARD.",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The &quot;Small Scale Dairy Unit (SSDU)&quot; has been launched by the Department of Animal Husbandry &amp; Veterinary Services, U.T. Administration of Daman &amp; Diu and Dadra &amp; Nagar Haveli. It aims to promote dairy development by supporting the establishment of a small-scale dairy unit with indigenous Gir cows. Through this scheme, financial assistance in the form of capital subsidy and back-ended subsidy is provided to beneficiaries for the purchase of milch cows, construction of cattle sheds, and procurement of feed, equipment, and insurance coverage.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "**Assistance for 10 Cows:**\n<br>\n\n**Sr. No.****Activity****Cost (₹)****U.T. Administration Subsidy****Under DEDS – Beneficiary Gets Subsidy**1Cost of 10 milch cows, including transportation cost (@ ₹60,000 per cow)₹6,00,000/-₹1,50,000/- (25% of purchase cost)Back-ended subsidy from NABARD: ₹1,50,000/- (25% for General) or ₹1,99,980/- (33.33% for SC/ST)2Cost towards cattle shed, water tank, store room, automatic drinking system, etc.₹2,60,000/-₹1,25,000/- (50% of construction cost)344 bags of cattle feed (each of 50 kg) (44 bags × 10 @ ₹600/- per bag)₹2,64,000/-₹1,32,000/- (50% of purchase cost)444 kg of mineral mixture (each of 1 kg) (44 kg × 2 @ ₹80/- per bag)₹35,200/-₹17,600/- (50% of purchase cost)5Purchase of a milking machine (once in a lifetime)₹65,000/-₹33,700/- (75% of purchase cost)6Purchase of an electric-driven chaff cutter (once in a lifetime)₹38,000/-₹15,000/- (75% of purchase cost)7Cost of insurance for 3 years (approx. @ ₹5,400/- per animal)₹54,000/-₹27,000/- (50% for General) or ₹40,500 (75% for SC/ST)<br>\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "exclusions_md": "<br>\n\n",
        "detailedDescription": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "The \"Small Scale Dairy Unit (SSDU)\" has been launched by the Department of Animal Husbandry & Veterinary Services, U.T. Administration of Daman & Diu and Dadra & Nagar Haveli. It aims to promote dairy development by supporting the establishment of a small-scale dairy unit with indigenous Gir cows. Through this scheme, financial assistance in the form of capital subsidy and back-ended subsidy is provided to beneficiaries for the purchase of milch cows, construction of cattle sheds, and procurement of feed, equipment, and insurance coverage."
              }
            ]
